        "subject": "LU-9341 llite: Do not lock the world for append",
        "message": "LU-9341 llite: Do not lock the world for append\n\nThis patch does a few things to guarantee append write\natomicity from multiple processes and multiple clients\nwithout having to instantiate and lock the entire layout.\n\n1. Before starting an append i/o, the client requests a\nlock to EOF on the first object of the file.  It finds the\nfirst object by requesting a lock on the first byte of the\nfile in clio, then switching to an EOF lock request at the\nLDLM layer.  This lock is held throughout the i/o.\nThis guarantees exclusion with appends from other clients.\nThanks to Bobijam for this idea.\n\nLocking to EOF at the LDLM layer is necessary so we are\nguaranteed we can use this lock for any i/o to this object.\n\n2. After taking this lock, the client gets the file size\nand sets the position of the append i/o and does it like\nany other write.  This means it does not check size again if\nthe i/o is restarted or for each stripe of the i/o\nseparately.  This guarantees the write is all in one place\nin the file.  (This does not prevent non-append writes\nfrom writing in the middle of this space, but this is always\nthe case and is a legitimate race.)  Because getting the\nsize occurs under the \"append\" lock (see 1.), no other\nappend will check size until this write is complete.\n\n3. To guarantee exclusion with other append writes on the\nsame client, which could share the LDLM lock, we convert\nappend writes to hold the range lock across i/o restarts.\n\nNote that because clients without this special\n\"append lock\" behavior attempt to lock the full layout,\nincluding the first object, we achieve exclusion with\nthese clients as well.\n\nN.B. This isn't quite done, but except for released files,\nI believe it's correct.\n\nTODO:\n- Add comments & debug messages in code\n- Figure out how this works with released files\n- Possibly add special test?  There are several append\ntests already, and it's not immediately obvious what to add\nhere.  Could just be a test to verify append does *not*\nalways instantiate full PFL layout.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0100746292526b1f989d277f0a07bc711191f441\n"
      },
